 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>A Druid so Tall</span><br>  Posts: 802<br> <font color=#333399>(7/30/02 2:53:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2848.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: kunark</span><hr size=1> I would just like to point out, that "Succor" and "Lesser Succor" are identical spells except for:<br>
<br>
Casting time:  Lesser Succor casts about 1 second slower.<br>
<br>
Mana Cost: Lesser Succor costs 150+300 mana from everyone (Succor costs 100+150 from everyone).<br>
<br>
All other features of these spells are identical.<br>
<br>
=-=-=-=-=<br>
<br>
My input on this issues now that "Safe Spots" have changed a lot and new zones introduced.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Druids *should* purchase these evac spells:<br>
----------<br>
*Lesser Succor<br>
<br>
*Succor: East (It is yet another zone you can port to, even if it is only a zone away).<br>
<br>
*Succor: Butcher (a totally safe evac location for everyone)<br>
<br>
* Wind North/South<br>
<br>
* Succor<br>
<br>
NOTE: <br>
---------------<br>
<br>
The other succor spells are not necessary, and you will not be upset that you do not have them. If you feel like getting them, get them.<br>
<br>
